  "body": "Abstract this construction https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/7a553443be393b93fcb75694d1cc343564cac1cd/packages/lodestar/src/network/util.ts#L141-L150 to properly test it and make sure it doesn't leak\r\n```ts\r\nabortableTimeoutCallback(\r\n  fn: () => Promise<void>,\r\n  timeoutMs: number,\r\n  signal: AbortSignal\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nYeah, I think that would be really useful to pull into its own function. Basically like `setTimeout` but with a signal. (and not supporting the 'evil' extra arguments that `setTimeout` supports)\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @wemeetagain in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/1600#r500404877_",
